DataElement.preferredDefinition: A type of chromatography in which separation of a mixture is achieved by passing a sample in a stream of liquid solvent through some form of material that will provide resistance by virtue of chemical interactions between the components of the sample and the material.:A part, a fragment of a whole._A place of termination or completion. This may be a primary or secondary outcome variable used to judge the effectiveness of a treatment._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Double-precision floating point number (64-bit IEEE 7540).
